Class AppState

java.lang.Object
AppState
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class AppState extends Object implements Serializable
Singleton container that stores the application's core data lists for serialization. updateSelfState() captures current lists from DbMgr singletons. restoreOtherState() writes stored lists back into the DbMgr singletons.

    • updateSelfState

      public void updateSelfState()
      Capture the current lists from DbMgr singletons into this AppState. Expects each DbMgr to expose a read accessor such as getAll().

    • restoreOtherState

      public void restoreOtherState()
      Restore stored lists back into the DbMgr singletons. Expects each DbMgr to provide a setter such as setAll(List).
